# Truegrynd – Testing Guidelines

## Tools
- **Vitest**: unit tests and component tests
- **Testing Library**: component rendering and user interactions
- **Playwright**: e2e smoke tests (Chromium only in MVP)
- **MSW**: mock Supabase/API calls in unit tests

## What to Always Test
- Score submission logic (especially Smart Proof top 10% threshold)
- Leaderboard sorting and filtering
- Finisher Card data formatting (rank %, time format)
- Form validation schemas (Zod)
- Auth redirects

## What to Skip
- Pure UI components with no logic
- Next.js layout files
- Third-party library wrappers

## Patterns
- Arrange / Act / Assert structure
- Use `userEvent` over `fireEvent` for realistic interactions
- Query by user-visible text/role — never by test-id unless no other option
- Mock Supabase at the service layer, not inside components
- 70% coverage baseline target

## E2E (Playwright)
- Only smoke tests in MVP: homepage loads, auth flow, score submission
- `e2e/smoke.spec.ts` — gated behind `pre-push` hook
- `baseURL` defaults to `localhost:3000`

## Commands
```bash
pnpm test          # watch mode
pnpm test:run      # single run
pnpm coverage      # with coverage report
pnpm e2e           # playwright
pnpm e2e:headed    # playwright with browser visible
```
